diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 4fc1736..433678e 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -63,6 +63,34 @@ Requirements:
 
 See https://github.com/Marus/cortex-debug/wiki for usage information. This needs some help from the community. See https://github.com/Marus/cortex-debug/blob/master/debug_attributes.md for a summary of all properties that are available in your `launch.json`
 
+### Non-Cortex and C2000 targets
+
+Set `"targetCore": "c2000"` or `"targetCore": "custom"` when the GDB server is OpenOCD or an externally managed server but the core is not ARM Cortex-M. In this mode Cortex-Debug does not guess `arm-none-eabi-gdb`, and it does not send Cortex-M-oriented OpenOCD defaults such as `monitor reset halt` or `monitor halt`. Provide the target-specific GDB explicitly with `gdbPath`, or provide a matching `toolchainPrefix`.
+
+Example for attaching to a TI C2000/C28x core exposed by an already running OpenOCD instance:
+
+```json
+{
+    "name": "F28M35x C28x via OpenOCD",
+    "type": "cortex-debug",
+    "request": "attach",
+    "servertype": "external",
+    "targetCore": "c2000",
+    "cwd": "${workspaceFolder}",
+    "executable": "${workspaceFolder}/build/c28x.out",
+    "gdbPath": "C:/ti/ccs/tools/compiler/ti-cgt-c2000/bin/c28x-gdb.exe",
+    "gdbTarget": "localhost:3334",
+    "postAttachCommands": [
+        "interpreter-exec console \"monitor halt\""
+    ],
+    "overrideResetCommands": [
+        "interpreter-exec console \"monitor reset halt\""
+    ]
+}
+```
+
+For a heterogeneous MCU such as an ARM Cortex-M3 plus a TI C28x, create two VS Code debug configurations and launch them as parallel or chained sessions. Use `"targetCore": "cortex-m"` with an ARM GDB for the Cortex-M side, and `"targetCore": "c2000"` with a C2000-capable GDB for the C28x side. Each session should connect to the GDB port that OpenOCD assigned to that specific core.
+
 ## How to Build from sources
 
 Make sure you have git, NodeJS and typescript installed on your PC before you begin. See: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/setup/additional-components
